                        <interp inst="t18390304-name-843" type="given" value="GRIFFITH"></interp>GRIFFITH THOMAS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a linen-draper, and live in Oxford-street The prisoner was working for me, behind the counter in my shop—I suspected him, followed him into the area, and charged him with robbing me—he produced this print from under his apron—he had no business to tones it—it is worth 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You had repairs going on, and he we repairing your things? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—a fellow-workman of his gave me information—he is still at work at the house—the prisoner was in the kitchen when he saw me, and went into the area, bat could not get into the street—I went up to him and said, "You axe robbing me"—he said he hoped I should forgive him, and he was very sorry for what he had some—there was a female servant in the kitchen—I could not observe whether he had been speaking to her—he must have passed her to go to the area—she has left my service—he had no jacket on—he had been rating for me for about a fortnight—there were many things of much greater value about, but he could not have taken them, without opening. wrappers.</p>
